Thinking about how starving families would abandon their newborn children outside on the streets in Shanghai's slums where they would be devoured alive by rats and wild dogs so St. John the Wonderworker walked alone all night finding and rescuing them. He literally never slept.

People got killed there every night, super dangerous streets full of bandits. Still zero fear, walked alone for hours listening for cries. Just an insanely tough, hardcore guy. St. John of Shanghai. Look him up.
they managed to get enough grains to keep everyone alive

This verse from 1 Corinthians 5 is actually about excommunication from the church, but if you don't know the correct interpretation, you would assume St. Paul is telling them to physically bring that man over to the devil who will then devour his body like a cannibal

Like if you are a happy pagan from the Conan the Barbarian world and you somehow get these Bible passages on a scroll you would read it as St. Paul suggesting they throw the guy into a pit inside which some monster is housed where it will maul and consume him
I really like cranking the little handle on old school ones, makes you feel like a little oompa loompa in Willie Wonka's factory operating some wacky manual machinery

Same with unlocking car doors with the key itself rather than pressing a button, it's like an apartment door, feels satisfying to use, tactile. Nowadays some cars apparently don't even have an ignition key and it's a button you press too, would be so depressing and dull to drive
